1 SECTION 3. OTHER FUNDS - FOUNDATION AID STABILIZATION FUND. The other
2 funds line item in subdivision 1 of section 1 of this Act includes the sum of $157,000,000 from
3 the foundation aid stabilization fund for integrated formula payments.
4 SECTION 4. OTHER FUNDS - STRATEGIC INVESTMENT AND IMPROVEMENTS FUND.
5 The other funds line item in subdivision 1 of section 1 of this Act includes the sum of
6 $13,993,086 from the strategic investment and improvements fund for integrated formula
7 payments.
8 SECTION 5. INTEGRATED FORMULA PAYMENTS AND SPECIAL EDUCATION
9 CONTRACTS EXPENDITURE AUTHORITY. The superintendent of public instruction may
10 expend funds included in the integrated formula payments and grants - special education
11 contracts line items in subdivision 1 of section 1 of this Act for paying grants for educational
12 services that were due in the 2023-25 biennium but which were not filed, claimed, or properly
13 supported by the education provider until after June 30, 2025. To be reimbursed under this
14 section, claims must be properly supported and filed with the superintendent of public
15 instruction by June 30, 2026.
16 SECTION 6. GIFTED AND TALENTED PROGRAM. The sum of $800,000, included in the
17 integrated formula payments line item in subdivision 1 of section 1 of this Act, must be
18 distributed to reimburse school districts or special education units for gifted and talented
19 programs upon the submission of an application that is approved in accordance with guidelines
20 adopted by the superintendent of public instruction. The superintendent of public instruction
21 shall encourage cooperative efforts for gifted and talented programs among school districts and
22 special education units.
23 SECTION 7. MEDICAID MATCHING FUNDING AND SCHOOL APPROVAL -
24 WITHHOLDING AND DISTRIBUTION.
25 1. State school aid payments for special education must be reduced by the amount of
26 matching funds required to be paid by school districts or special education units for
27 students participating in the Medicaid program for the biennium beginning July 1,
28 2025, and ending June 30, 2027. Special education funds equal to the amount of the
29 matching funds required to be paid by the school district or special education unit must
30 be paid by the superintendent of public instruction to the department of health and
31 human services on behalf of the school district or unit.
